<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Qanimaru on 02-12-2002 11:59 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">The advantage of GVD is that you can carry 105 invis potions in 2 slots as long as you dedicate one of your inventory slots to a delux toolbox (10 slots, no weight reduction).

It takes longer to cast than an invis potion. It costs the same per usage as potions. You must equip the GVD to use it (in range slot). But your inventory will thank you for the available space for other stuff.

I used to carry 6-8 invis potions and make a trip to re-purchase about once a week before I got my GVD. 2-3 potions would have been enough if it didn't sometimes wear off in less than 30 seconds back to back). Now I have a stack of 20 Class-5 Mana Batteries and I haven't been back to restock in over a month. Course, I'll have to bring my Gold Visa again when I do. :P 55p * 20 Batteries = 1100p.

If you have the Haze Panther Eyes and want one, I know two tinkerers on E'ci who both have 200+ skill and seem to get success in about 1 out of 5 tries (Limited tests so far). Send me a tell in game and I'll point you to them. I can't quote you a price though.

Qanimaru Willowmoon...
60th Cleric of E'ci
Forlorn
</TEXTAREA>
